participant_id.Description: Unique BIDS identifier for the participant in this study.

subjectkey.Description: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject

src_subject_id.Description: Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project

interview_age.Description: Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging. | Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

interview_date.Description: Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY

sex.Description: Sex of subject at birth | M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

eventname.Description: The event name for which the data was collected

iqc_initial_rec.Description: DAIC has received at least one series for this pGUID

iqc_event_qcd.Description: DAIC has received full protocol for this pGUID and it has been QC'ed

iqc_event_rsfmri_autoqcd.Description: rsfMRI: Decide whether rsfmri series in a given pguidevent pass qc or not. | 1 = all rsfmri series pass qc;  0 = NOT all rsfmri series pass qc

Levels.0: NOT all rsfmri series pass qc

iqc_eventcomplete.Description: DAIC has received entire protocol for this pGUID (at least one T1, at least T2, at least one dMRI, at least 3 rsfMRI runs with corresponding field maps, and at least 2 runs of each task with corresponding field maps)

iqc_eventcomplete_c_pc_qc.Description: DAIC has received full protocol for this pGUID and everything was complete, passed QC and protocol compliance

iqc_sst_ep_datetime_found.Description: Eprime SST file found and readable | 0= Not Found; 1= Found

iqc_sst_ep_file_resf.Description: Diagnostic number, formed by summing:       File found?   0  -->  [Unable to find file];    Encoding:   1,      2  -->  ['utf-8','utf-16'];   Separator: 10,     20  -->  [Tab, Comma];    Quoted rows?   0,    100  -->  [No, Yes];  Start_time_info:              0,   1000  -->  [Found, Unable to extract]; File read?  0,  10000  -->  [Yes,   Unable to read];  Filename contains '()':   100000  -->  [Yes];   Experiment matches filename?    1000000  -->  [No]
